      "And the buyer pool is whatever walks through the door. Demand — and stronger prices — exist in other markets: gold trades at persistent regional premiums, from Shanghai to Mumbai to the Gulf. But duties, export licensing, logistics, and capital controls wall a local dealer off from them. Inventory that sits slow on your counter may be bid up a continent away, with no clean pathway to reach it.",
    ],
